si.t:
The WWF Coastal Communities Initiative works with Indigenous Peoples and local communities, regional networks, government authorities and non-profits to accelerate and scale coastal community-led conservation in 32 countries around the world. The scaling by design approach includes: 1) Scaling out: replicating the most effective community-led conservation solutions; 2) Scaling up: embedding solutions into national and regional actions, policies or legislation; and 3) Scaling deep: building coastal community capacity and promoting the adoption of the solutions through learning and sharing. By 2030, the Coastal Communities Initiative will secure at least 4 million km2 of critical coastal ecosystems vital to the food security and livelihoods of millions of vulnerable people.
The initiative addresses;
Overfishingclimate change impactsbiodiversity losscoastal degradation.
